# Free Tier Constraints

- Assume this project runs on:
  - Vercel Free
  - Supabase Free
  - GitHub Free
- Prefer recommendations and designs that work within free-tier limits first (bandwidth, compute, DB size, connection limits, CI usage).
- Avoid suggesting paid services/add-ons by default; present free-tier-compatible options first.
- When a paid upgrade would materially improve reliability/performance/security, clearly label it as optional and explain trade-offs.
- For database access in serverless contexts, prioritize connection-safe patterns (pooling, lightweight queries, caching where appropriate).
- Keep operational overhead low: favor simple, maintainable solutions over complex infra.
